        "1656046443b1b2d9f5-0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Do loud environments often make you feel panicked or overwhelmed? Well, you’re not alone. Noise sensitivity anxiety is a common issue, and while different people experience it to varying degrees, it can be difficult to deal with for anyone.<\/p><p>For some people, anxiety can be triggered by unexpected noises such as fireworks, backfiring cars, or sudden shouting. For others, simple everyday sounds such as chewing, music, and coughing can cause significant distress. At the more extreme end of the scale, noise sensitivity issues can have a big impact on people’s lives, leading them to avoid certain situations and become socially isolated.<\/p><p>In this post, we look at the common kinds of noise sensitivity and some of the ways you can reduce anxiety in loud environments to live a more comfortable life.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "1656046443b1b2d9f5-0"
      ],
