    "16604607234acd9044": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "166046072211f39075-0": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Common types of noise-related sensitivity and anxiety",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "166046072211f39075-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>There are several types of sensitivity and anxiety caused by loud and distressing noises, some of which have overlapping symptoms. Some of the most common include:<\/p>"
          }
        },
        "d6a51c5b-3b59-4ae3-b3d3-43f0ad37ee2e": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Phonophobia",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "fd098bcc-1457-415e-bcbc-9eb51f262215": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Phonophobia, or fear of noise, is characterized by anxiety in the presence of loud noises. This could include anything from applause to passing vehicles, music, shouting, and more. Understandably, this can make crowded areas and social situations very difficult for people to deal with.<\/p>"
          }
        },
        "4bddc5cf-f6dc-420b-8158-3c41639b641b": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Misophonia",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "05e7bc80-2a3c-419d-a3cd-8e5269dd8c84": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Misophonia<\/span> is a condition involving repulsion and anger in response to noises made by others. For example, someone may become intensely angry at the sound of chewing, finger-tapping, or coughing. This can lead to strained relationships with others and avoidance of social situations.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "166046072211f39075-0",
