    "16581501774a32acf8": {
      "type": "loop-article-img-txt",
      "blocks": {
        "81a12173-0171-4d1e-9fe4-12e07aac5bcf": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Try not to avoid loud places",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "16581501770ad7ecad-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Yes, you read that right. It might sound counterintuitive, but hear us out. Noise sensitivity issues often elicit a fight or flight response, so one of the most common effects is for people to simply avoid loud places altogether. However, not only can this have a serious impact on their quality of life, it can actually make the problem even worse when they inevitably do encounter loud noises.<\/p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        },
        "b6d13c7c-ae41-4912-b692-bd1efbe55088": {
          "type": "button",
          "settings": {
            "button_label": "More on noise sensitivity",
            "button_link": "https:\/\/www.loopearplugs.com\/pages\/noise-sensitivity",
            "button_bgcolor": "",
            "button_txtcolor": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "81a12173-0171-4d1e-9fe4-12e07aac5bcf",
